  "body": "We have a code that use the client.SendTransaction to interact with a smart contract.\r\n\r\nwith 1.11.5 everything works, switching to 1.13.5 we receive an error from the smart contract as if we sent it ETH.\r\nthe error is catched by the receive() function implemented in the smart contract (that doesn not accept ETH).\r\n\r\nswitching back to 1.11.5 with the same code there is no such error.\r\n\r\nthe error appear with both a view function or a write function or even accessing a public variable.\r\n\r\nWhat has changed between 1.11.5 and 1.13.5 that could lead to such break? some obscure default?\r\n",
