    "body": "The test is using hardhat but the same error has been proven on polygon and ethereum testnet\r\n\r\nwe call \r\n`ethclient.Client.CallContract(context.Background() , msg, nil)`\r\n\r\nwhere msg is \r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\nmsg := ethereum.CallMsg{\r\n\t\tFrom:     0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000,\r\n\t\tTo:        0xB5AE3e2883934457cb593793f034b401867e1372,\r\n\t\tGas:       0x0,\r\n\t\tGasPrice:  0,\r\n\t\tGasFeeCap: 0,\r\n\t\tGasTipCap: 0,\r\n\t\tValue:     0,\r\n\t\tData:      []uint8{0x72, 0x84, 0xe4, 0x16},\r\n\t}\r\n```\r\n\r\nprinting msg in the log results in this\r\n\r\n`ethereum.CallMsg{From:0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000, To:0xB5AE3e2883934457cb593793f034b401867e1372, Gas:0x0, GasPrice:0, GasFeeCap:0, GasTipCap:0, Value:0, Data:[]uint8{0x72, 0x84, 0xe4, 0x16}, AccessList:types.AccessList(nil)}`\r\n\r\nthe response is\r\n\r\n>  Error: VM Exception while processing transaction: revert This contract does not accept token\"\r\n\r\n(that is the message in the solidity contract throw by\r\n\r\n\r\n    receive() external payable {\r\n        revert(\"This contract does not accept token\");\r\n    }\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\njust switching in go.mod \r\ngithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum v1.13.5\r\nwith\r\ngithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum v1.11.5\r\n\r\nand it worrks\r\n",
